Remembered the beta.
2nd go: ground to b4, take, 4-13, fell, hung for less than a minute, pulled back on, then went to the top.

Beta improvements:
Rest at b2 there is a RH side-pull crimp to switch it up.
I Do actually briefly use the kneebar at b10, but not for very long. 
At b11, setting up for the LH undercling, there’s a slightly higher right foot, to get established in the undercling. Then for the undercling move, it’s easier to hike the right foot higher to the flat shelf.
At b13, RH to the sloper, then instead of bumping RH to the crystal, bump it to the slot instead. Then LH to the crystal.
At the last rest above b17, there’s a small RH crimp side pull

Notes:
1st: ground to 12. Boulder was cleanest I’ve ever done it. After big left hand slap, hop left foot up to shitty scoop, hight right foot up above triangle, right hand straight to undercling. 
2nd: skipped boulder, tried to work the top while tired, took several times. Wired the last 2 moves.
Location: Colorado > Boulder > Flatirons > South > Seal Rock

Notes:
1st: ground to b10. Best link from the ground
2nd: worked boulder a few times
3rd: while pretty tired, linked ground to 10 again.
Location: Colorado > Boulder > Flatirons > South > Seal Rock

Notes:
Managed 4 attempts:
1st warm up to b6 (with takes)
2nd linked 8-top
3rd linked 5-top (best link yet!)
4th ended up a bit too tired for the boulder, but linked 3-11, then flamed out.
Location: Colorado > Boulder > Flatirons > South > Seal Rock

Notes:
1st go Linked 3-12, 12-16, 16-18. Took a nice whipper on the last move. 

2nd go linked 4-11, but was fatigued from the start, so still a good link while tired. 

Use Adam’s beta at b13: RH on the higher good side pull, left hand to the sloper, right foot up and in, then go to the tick in the dish.
Also learned I should maybe climb a little slower from b8-11, and I can actually get a couple quick shakes through that section, even when tired.
Location: Colorado > Boulder > Flatirons > South > Seal Rock

Notes:
Holy shit… the pebble at the start broke…. Supposedly somebody has the pebble and might glue it back on… anyway, the boulder still goes without the nubbin, as I got to b2 first attempt by skipping the pebble and going to the undercling/Gaston right above it with right hand instead. slightly harder but doesn't change the grade for me. Finished warming up going to b8 couple bolts at a time.
2nd go - ground to b8 (new highest link from ground. Then b8-11, then b11-13. Diminishing returns… need to learn how to rest better.
3rd go did just the boulder to b2. Use a left foot under the big undercling instead of heel hooking the undercling, it’s sets up the next high right foot much better.
Location: Colorado > Boulder > Flatirons > South > Seal Rock

Notes:
Still getting mega pumped from bolts 8-11. I need to do more e sure de training; and figure out how to at least get a couple good shakes at the knee bar(s). 
2nd go: b4-11, figured out how to get a a little shake at the kneebar, but still pumped going for bolt 12 on the undercling. Then did b13-16. I really need to train endurance for bolts 10-14. For the undercling move, I can get a higher left foot on a little spike to help get my right foot up on the flat edge before going to the “jugs”. Also, maybe I want to use the sloper at bolt 13 instead of the Gaston crimp.
5th bolt get right foot low on the ramp, right hand up to pinch, left hand to better undercling, right foot a little higher on the ramp, then high left foot. Bolt 8, just after the rest out right, there is a higher right foot to get to the left hand pinch (just above slot)
Location: Colorado > Boulder > Flatirons > South > Seal Rock
